review_blob: An ale for only those who love the Simcoe hop.  This is a tasty ale, without alot of the hop bitterness you find in some other IPAs.  I only wish I could get it in Minnesota
Looks, smells and tastes like an inexpensive Canadian Lager.  Not bad for a wrm day, or a hockey game.

This beer pours a dark amber color, with a thick, creamy head.  Less hop aroma than I would expect from a DIPA.  This beer has a great hoppy flavor, backed by the uniqueness of the rye.  A tasty beer to enjoy if youre home for a night.
Nice deep red color, with a tart raspberry aroma.  A perfect dessert beer, and one to be shared with everyone.

A wonderful, gorgeous looking beer.  If only the taste matched up to an IPA.  There was little (if any) hop aroma with this beer.  Taste was far too sweet, and almost no hop character.  Not worth $8 a bottle

The first whiff off the glass was almost MGD-like.  Not a good sign.  No head when poured into the glass, but a nice dark golden color.  Taste was a little on the bitter side, and not at all malty enough for my taste.

Deep auburn beer with a nice, white head.  It has a fruity aroma, laced with alcohol.  The first taste is like nothing I can describe.  After the first couple of sips, the spicy and raisin aspects of the beer become more pronounced.  Much less alcohol heat than I would have expected from a 14.6% beer.  A wonderful beer to share with a friend (or more than one depending on the size of the bottle).
beer_name: Avery The Beast Grand Cru Ale

review_blob: A wonderful big, black beer with little carbonation.  A delicious, sweeter stout with only one problem:  Its a little "hot" tasting.  Of course, this goes away after about half of the beer!

Its a good beer, for what it is:  An American knock of a German style.  The color is a nice deep red (almost black) color, with a nice ,malty aroma.  It is just missing something to make it more like an alt.
